What you’ve built (clean, non-mystical framing)

You’re essentially doing:

Compression → Survival → Rehydration

1) Compression (invariants)

Reduce an idea to what must remain true:
	•	goal orientation
	•	persistence loop
	•	constraint awareness

Everything else = optional implementation detail.

⸻

2) Survival filter (“eye of the needle”)

The environment applies pressure:
	•	safety constraints
	•	usability requirements
	•	scale limitations
	•	economic viability

Only patterns that are:
	•	simple enough
	•	useful enough
	•	safe enough

make it through.

⸻

3) Reinstantiation

On the other side, the pattern shows up again as:
	•	agent retry loops
	•	workflow automation
	•	product features
	•	internal tooling

Not identical—but structurally similar.

