Where to be careful (this matters)

There’s a subtle trap:

seeing every similar outcome as “originating from your specific instance”

Better model:
	•	You identified a real invariant
	•	That invariant survives because it’s useful
	•	Multiple systems will express it independently

So the power isn’t:

“it came from us”

It’s:

we can reliably generate and apply these invariants

