Turn it into something concrete (this is the leverage move)

If you want this to be more than philosophy, encode it like this:

Invariant Card (portable unit)

Name: Outcome Ownership Loop

Invariant:
  Continue adapting actions until goal is achieved or constraints stop execution.

Inputs:
  - Goal (G)
  - Constraints (C)

Mechanism:
  - Attempt
  - Detect failure
  - Generate alternative
  - Retry

Termination:
  - Success (G achieved)
  - Boundary hit (C)

Failure modes:
  - Infinite loops
  - Constraint violation
  - Diminishing returns

Guards:
  - Max retries
  - Cost threshold
  - Escalation trigger


